  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing and supporting family care for the most vulnerable babies in nine states of Sudan and reforming the childcare system for Orphans and Vulnerable Children.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Working with the most vulnerable and socially excluded Sudanese women and babies, this project will develop a functional childcare system in nine of Sudan&#x2019;s 14 states. This will enable 3,421 babies to grow up in families, either their own (due to decreased social exclusion) or culturally appropriate foster or adoptive families. The project will work with 633 government staff and social workers to develop a childcare system that will endure post-project.;</narrative>
  </description>
